<title>INDIA: India needs 3-5 pct inflation for convertibility.</title>
<headline>India needs 3-5 pct inflation for convertibility.</headline>
<dateline>BOMBAY 1997-06-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>India needs 3-5 percent annual inflation as a pre-condition for convertibility of the rupee, a panel charged with plotting the path toward freeing the exchange rate recommended in a report presented to the Reserve Bank of India on Tuesday.</p>
<p>-- Bombay newsroom +91-22-265 9000</p>
